text:
Histadrut President Arnon Bar-David presented today (Wednesday) the main points of agreement between the Histadrut and the Ministry of Finance regarding the 2025 budget.
“The Israeli spirit is to move forward and deal with the situation,” Bar-David said. “We are all on the front lines in all workplaces, spaces and unions, in NAMAT, in committees. We have felt the pressure in the last year, we are at a level of madness that I don’t remember before.”
“Always in times of need, the Histadrut lent a shoulder. Out of commitment to the economy, a commitment to the values ​​that the Histadrut committed to when it was founded. I debated whether to enter into an agreement with such a government which has issues relating to the number of ministers, coalition funding. The decision was to move forward with national responsibility: in the end there is a country, in the end there is an economy and in the end there is hope. ”.
Arnon Bar-David presents the agreement with the Histadrut-led Treasury (photo: Histadrut spokesperson)
“We are faced with a difficult government, with a minister not from our camp, who sees everything the opposite of us”, said Bar-David referring to the negotiations on the agreement: “The Treasury came, as in every budget, and he took all his dreams out of the drawer. This time his dreams were achievable. Because the situation is terrible, where will they get the money from? everything in the drawers.”
He detailed some of the provisions proposed by the Treasury and abandoned the chapter following a struggle. “The first feather in our cap is the training funds. They wanted to tax them. It is their dream that they spend every year. Saving training funds is our basis for changing cars, marrying a child, living. This was in our minds, and we were able to prevent harm from being done to them.” On reversing the minimum wage freeze, he said: “It saves a lot of money, but it would hurt workers at the lowest levels. There was strong pressure on me to have a freeze in the public sector, but that it won’t happen. In April the minimum wage will rise to around NIS 6,200, much more than we once thought.
Regarding the freezing of pensions in the budget, he said: “This is another red flag for the Histadrut, we managed to lower that too.” On the freezing of benefits: “Apparently this is none of our business. The state can decide to freeze benefits. Here we had excellent cooperation with the Shas ministers. Together with them we managed to prevent this.”
The Histadrut president added: “We have received 4 long weekends for the public sector every year in 2025 and 2026. It will be a two-year pilot project, and in Israel it is customary to say that everything temporary is permanent. “
On the Settlements Act he said: “There were some very problematic things and we managed to remove everything, and there is also a section that says if there is anything affecting workers in the Settlements Act, it will be agreed by l ‘Histadrut We have removed a number of things that would harm state employees.”
The main points of the agreement The agreements provide that the salary increases provided for in the framework agreement for public employees will be punctual – 2% starting from the December 2024 salary, 1.5% from the April 2025 salary and 1.5% from the April 2026 salary – inclusive of seniority and increases the rank. At the same time, there will be a temporary compensation of employee wages at the rate of 2.29% between December 2024 and December 2025, and at the rate of 1.2% in 2026. At the end of 2026, the compensation will be canceled.
According to the agreements, the compensation will not reduce the cumulative and budgetary pension salary of public sector employees and will not affect final payments (last payment to the employee who finishes working). Legislation will be promoted to apply a similar retrenchment mechanism to all public sector employees.
Instead of offsetting two days of recovery as the Treasury wanted, one day of recovery will be offset in 2025 for all workers in the economy. The amount of recovery fees will remain unchanged. The compensated funds will be used for grants and rewards for reservists.
In accordance with the agreements and after the Histadrut’s struggle, the freezing of the minimum wage and disability and old-age benefits were eliminated from the settlement bill. The freezing of the update of pensions of employees insured in a budgetary pension, in accordance with the consumer price index, and the increase in employee participation in a budgetary pension has also decreased. In relation to the suspension of the increase in the tax benefit for the use of the pension allowance, it has been agreed that the increase will be suspended for one year and will return from 2026.
In parallel, the Histadrut and the Treasury agreed to update agreements with security and cleaning contractors in the public sector and to take action to increase the minimum wage in the cleaning sector by promoting the signing of an expansion order to the contracted sector sector collective agreement signed in November 2021. It was also agreed to complete the necessary legislative changes in order to implement the pensioners annex, detailed in the 2016 and 2023 framework agreements. It was decided to keep a discussion and dialogue with the Histadrut on issues that have consequences for employees, which are detailed in the Settlements Law.
